      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 2 for MRL 3.",
      "rationale": "Experimental test conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid temperature, and hematocrit) were documented and matched to the simulation boundary conditions within stated tolerances. Achieved Gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 2 for MRL 3.",
      "rationale": "Predicted normalized hemolysis index (NIH) values were compared to FDA pump experimental measurements at all five operating points. Mean absolute error was 8.4%, within the acceptance band. Achieved Gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 2 for MRL 3.",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI is the relative hemolysis index (RH), which directly maps to the clinical acceptance criterion RH < 1. Scalar NIH is derived from the power-law hemolysis model applied to the shear-stress field. Achieved Gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
